project uses pnpm

USE pnpm lint && pnpm lint:fix BEFORE EVERY COMMIT!!!

Run both from **repository root**.

What happens under the hood (root `package.json`):
- `pnpm lint` — `pnpm --filter @meriter/api lint` then `pnpm --filter @meriter/web lint`. API’s script runs eslint with `--fix` (may modify files); web’s `lint` has no `--fix` (check-only).
- `pnpm lint:fix` — same `@meriter/api` command as `pnpm lint`, then `pnpm --filter @meriter/web lint:fix` (eslint with `--fix` for web). Only the **web** step differs from `pnpm lint`.

Full command list and dev setup: see @local-dev-win.mdc or `docs/LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT_SETUP.md`.

### API tests and mongodb-memory-server

- API Jest runs use in-memory MongoDB (`mongodb-memory-server`). Temp data lives under `api/.cache/mongo-mem-test` (not `/tmp` for new runs).
- `pretest` sweeps **stale** orphaned dirs before each `pnpm --filter @meriter/api test`.
- If `/tmp/mongo-mem-*` or cache dirs accumulate (e.g. after Ctrl+C), run from repo root: `pnpm test:cleanup-mongo` (or `pnpm --filter @meriter/api test:cleanup-mongo -- --force` to kill live mongod and remove dirs).
